From Creamer Media in Johannesburg, this is the Real Economy Report. Sashnee Moodley: JSE-listed Redefine Properties continues to thrive amid a subdued environment, as a result of its strategy of investing where it believes the best market opportunities lie, while also catering to the demands of tenants. Simone Liedtke, who attended one of the company’s investor site visits, gives us some more detail. Simone Liedtke: During the investor site visit last month, Redefine Properties’ commercial asset manager Pieter Strydom spoke to Engineering News about how, in a continuous attempt to regain investor confidence, this event forms part of its long-term roll-out in terms of engagement, while also speaking to its investment strategy. Redefine Properties Commercial Asset Manager Pieter Strydom: Simone Liedtke: He further elaborated on how Redefine’s buildings in the Sandton and Rosebank nodes meet both the demands, and the requirements, of these areas, as well as those of the people who use them. Redefine Properties Commercial Asset Manager Pieter Strydom: Simone Liedtke: Keeping the tough South African environment in mind, Strydom cautiously gave Engineering News some insight into some of the trends that Redefine has identified, and whether or not he sees stabilization on the cards for the sector. Redefine Properties Commercial Asset Manager Pieter Strydom: Sashnee Moodley: That’s Creamer Media’s Real Economy Report. Join us again next week for more news and insight into South Africa’s real economy. Don’t forget to listen to the audio version of our Engineering News daily email newsletter.